		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Simple Saturn Game Hack</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I recently bought Pandemonium for my iPhone and as I played it, I realized it has a very Sonic the Hedgehog speed and feel to it.  Since there is no real Sonic game for the Saturn (3D blast sucks, Sonic Jam was a compilation and Sonic R is just a joke) and Pandemonium was originally a Saturn/PSX game, I got to thinkin: How hard would it be to hack in the 3D model for Sonic from Sonic R to replace the female character in Pandemonium?  She even does a forward flip when you double jump, making it an almost perfect transition for a Sonic model.  I don't know what kind of knowledge is out there and how difficult it is to hack Saturn games, but I figured if anyone knew, they would probably hang out around here.  I just think it would be hella cool to put Sonic in Pandemonium given the gameplay and level design is dead on to what a good Sonic game should be.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


